ived using the CGM window function\nat small scales as well as the linear matter power spectrum multiplied by a\nsimple anisotropic function at large scales. We apply this model to a mock\ngalaxy catalog at z=0.5, designed to resemble SDSS-III BOSS CMASS galaxies, and\nfind that our model can predict both the monopole and quadrupole power spectra\nof the host halos up to k<0.5 h/Mpc to within 5%.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 13 Nov 2016 17:49:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 18 Mar 2017 22:20:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-05-15"}
